http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Congress-re-nominates-Sikki-for-Assembly-seat/article14022005.ece

The Congress has re-nominated Ramanjit Singh Sikki as its candidate for the February 13 by-poll for the Khadoor Sahib Assembly seat in Punjab.The seat had fallen vacant after mr. Sikki, the sitting MLA had resigned over incidents of sacrilege in his constituency.“Congress president Sonia Gandhi has approved the proposal for the candidature of Ramanjit Singh Sikki, ex-MLA to contest by-election from Khadoor Sahib Assembly constituency as a party candidate in Punjab,” AICC general secretary Shakeel Ahmed said.Mr. Sikki will be pitted against Shiromani Akali Dal candidate Ravinder Singh Bramhapura. Mr. Sikki had defeated Ravinder’s father and senior Akali leader Ranjit Singh Brahmpura by a margin of over 3,000 votes in the 2012 Assembly polls.-PTI